JOel the Prophet, as Epiphanius ſaith, was a Bethorian of the Tribe of Ruben, and the ſon of Phatuel. It doth
not appeare out of the Book of his Propheſie under what King he propheſied or lived; But St Hierom writeth, that he prophecyed under the ſame Kings that Hoſea did, that is, Ʋzziah, Joatham, Ahaz, and Hezekiah, and he will have all his Propheſie to belong to the Kingdome of Judah only, and not alſo to Iſrael;
Act. 2.16. Ioel 2.28. he ſpake much concerning the comming of the Holy Ghoſt upon the Apoſtles, which St Peter the Apoſtle interpreted, and many, concerning that repentance which God requires in his Children: Moreover, as Epiphanius ſaith, he was buried honourably in his own Country.
